21/*! \file dns/rdataset.h
22 * \brief
23 * A DNS rdataset is a handle that can be associated with a collection of
24 * rdata all having a common owner name, class, and type.
25 *
26 * The dns_rdataset_t type is like a "virtual class". To actually use
27 * rdatasets, an implementation of the method suite (e.g. "slabbed rdata") is
28 * required.
29 *
30 * XXX &lt;more&gt; XXX
31 *
32 * MP:
33 *\li Clients of this module must impose any required synchronization.
34 *
35 * Reliability:
36 *\li No anticipated impact.
37 *
38 * Resources:
39 *\li TBS
40 *
41 * Security:
42 *\li No anticipated impact.
43 *
44 * Standards:
45 *\li None.
46 */
47
48#include <inttypes.h>
49#include <stdbool.h>
50
51#include <isc/lang.h>
52#include <isc/magic.h>
53#include <isc/stdtime.h>
54
55#include <dns/types.h>
56#include <dns/rdatastruct.h>

58ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS

60typedef enum {
61 dns_rdatasetadditional_fromauth,
62 dns_rdatasetadditional_fromcache,
63 dns_rdatasetadditional_fromglue
64} dns_rdatasetadditional_t;
65
66typedef struct dns_rdatasetmethods {
67 void (*disassociate)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
68 isc_result_t (*first)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
69 isc_result_t (*next)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
70 void (*current)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
71 dns_rdata_t *rdata);
72 void (*clone)(dns_rdataset_t *source,
73 dns_rdataset_t *target);
74 unsigned int (*count)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
75 isc_result_t (*addnoqname)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
76 const dns_name_t *name);
77 isc_result_t (*getnoqname)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
78 dns_name_t *name,
79 dns_rdataset_t *neg,
80 dns_rdataset_t *negsig);
81 isc_result_t (*addclosest)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
82 const dns_name_t *name);
83 isc_result_t (*getclosest)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
84 dns_name_t *name,
85 dns_rdataset_t *neg,
86 dns_rdataset_t *negsig);
87 void (*settrust)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
88 dns_trust_t trust);
89 void (*expire)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
90 void (*clearprefetch)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
91 void (*setownercase)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
92 const dns_name_t *name);
93 void (*getownercase)(const dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
94 dns_name_t *name);
95 isc_result_t (*addglue)(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
96 dns_dbversion_t *version,
97 dns_message_t *msg);
98} dns_rdatasetmethods_t;
99
100#define DNS_RDATASET_MAGIC ISC_MAGIC('D','N','S','R')
101#define DNS_RDATASET_VALID(set) ISC_MAGIC_VALID(set, DNS_RDATASET_MAGIC)
102
103/*%
104 * Direct use of this structure by clients is strongly discouraged, except
105 * for the 'link' field which may be used however the client wishes. The
106 * 'private', 'current', and 'index' fields MUST NOT be changed by clients.
107 * rdataset implementations may change any of the fields.
108 */
109struct dns_rdataset {
110 unsigned int magic; /* XXX ? */
111 dns_rdatasetmethods_t * methods;
112 ISC_LINK(dns_rdataset_t) link;
113
114 /*
115 * XXX do we need these, or should they be retrieved by methods?
116 * Leaning towards the latter, since they are not frequently required
117 * once you have the rdataset.
118 */
119 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass;
120 dns_rdatatype_t type;
121 dns_ttl_t ttl;
122 /*
123 * Stale ttl is used to see how long this RRset can still be used
124 * to serve to clients, after the TTL has expired.
125 */
126 dns_ttl_t stale_ttl;
127 dns_trust_t trust;
128 dns_rdatatype_t covers;
129
130 /*
131 * attributes
132 */
133 unsigned int attributes;
134
135 /*%
136 * the counter provides the starting point in the "cyclic" order.
137 * The value UINT32_MAX has a special meaning of "picking up a
138 * random value." in order to take care of databases that do not
139 * increment the counter.
140 */
141 uint32_t count;
142
143 /*
144 * This RRSIG RRset should be re-generated around this time.
145 * Only valid if DNS_RDATASETATTR_RESIGN is set in attributes.
146 */
147 isc_stdtime_t resign;
148
149 /*@{*/
150 /*%
151 * These are for use by the rdataset implementation, and MUST NOT
152 * be changed by clients.
153 */
154 void * private1;
155 void * private2;
156 void * private3;
157 unsigned int privateuint4;
158 void * private5;
159 const void * private6;
160 const void * private7;
161 /*@}*/
162
163};
164
165/*!
166 * \def DNS_RDATASETATTR_RENDERED
167 * Used by message.c to indicate that the rdataset was rendered.
168 *
169 * \def DNS_RDATASETATTR_TTLADJUSTED
170 * Used by message.c to indicate that the rdataset's rdata had differing
171 * TTL values, and the rdataset->ttl holds the smallest.
172 *
173 * \def DNS_RDATASETATTR_LOADORDER
174 * Output the RRset in load order.
175 */
176
177#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_NONE 0x00000000 /*%< No ordering. */
178#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_QUESTION 0x00000001
179#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_RENDERED 0x00000002 /*%< Used by message.c */
180#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_ANSWERED 0x00000004 /*%< Used by server. */
181#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_CACHE 0x00000008 /*%< Used by resolver. */
182#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_ANSWER 0x00000010 /*%< Used by resolver. */
183#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_ANSWERSIG 0x00000020 /*%< Used by resolver. */
184#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_EXTERNAL 0x00000040 /*%< Used by resolver. */
185#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_NCACHE 0x00000080 /*%< Used by resolver. */
186#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_CHAINING 0x00000100 /*%< Used by resolver. */
187#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_TTLADJUSTED 0x00000200 /*%< Used by message.c */
188#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_FIXEDORDER 0x00000400 /*%< Fixed ordering. */
189#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_RANDOMIZE 0x00000800 /*%< Random ordering. */
190#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_CHASE 0x00001000 /*%< Used by resolver. */
191#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_NXDOMAIN 0x00002000
192#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_NOQNAME 0x00004000
193#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_CHECKNAMES 0x00008000 /*%< Used by resolver. */
194#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_REQUIRED 0x00010000
195#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_REQUIREDGLUE DNS_RDATASETATTR_REQUIRED
196#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_LOADORDER 0x00020000
197#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_RESIGN 0x00040000
198#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_CLOSEST 0x00080000
199#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_OPTOUT 0x00100000 /*%< OPTOUT proof */
200#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_NEGATIVE 0x00200000
201#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_PREFETCH 0x00400000
202#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_CYCLIC 0x00800000 /*%< Cyclic ordering. */
203#define DNS_RDATASETATTR_STALE 0x01000000
204
205/*%
206 * _OMITDNSSEC:
207 * Omit DNSSEC records when rendering ncache records.
208 */
209#define DNS_RDATASETTOWIRE_OMITDNSSEC 0x0001

211void
212dns_rdataset_init(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
213/*%<
214 * Make 'rdataset' a valid, disassociated rdataset.
215 *
216 * Requires:
217 *\li 'rdataset' is not NULL.
218 *
219 * Ensures:
220 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, disassociated rdataset.
221 */
222
223void
224dns_rdataset_invalidate(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
225/*%<
226 * Invalidate 'rdataset'.
227 *
228 * Requires:
229 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, disassociated rdataset.
230 *
231 * Ensures:
232 *\li If assertion checking is enabled, future attempts to use 'rdataset'
233 * without initializing it will cause an assertion failure.
234 */
235
236void
237dns_rdataset_disassociate(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
238/*%<
239 * Disassociate 'rdataset' from its rdata, allowing it to be reused.
240 *
241 * Notes:
242 *\li The client must ensure it has no references to rdata in the rdataset
243 * before disassociating.
244 *
245 * Requires:
246 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, associated rdataset.
247 *
248 * Ensures:
249 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, disassociated rdataset.
250 */
251
252bool
253dns_rdataset_isassociated(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
254/*%<
255 * Is 'rdataset' associated?
256 *
257 * Requires:
258 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid rdataset.
259 *
260 * Returns:
261 *\li #true 'rdataset' is associated.
262 *\li #false 'rdataset' is not associated.
263 */
264
265void
266dns_rdataset_makequestion(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass,
267 dns_rdatatype_t type);
268/*%<
269 * Make 'rdataset' a valid, associated, question rdataset, with a
270 * question class of 'rdclass' and type 'type'.
271 *
272 * Notes:
273 *\li Question rdatasets have a class and type, but no rdata.
274 *
275 * Requires:
276 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, disassociated rdataset.
277 *
278 * Ensures:
279 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, associated, question rdataset.
280 */
281
282void
283dns_rdataset_clone(dns_rdataset_t *source, dns_rdataset_t *target);
284/*%<
285 * Make 'target' refer to the same rdataset as 'source'.
286 *
287 * Requires:
288 *\li 'source' is a valid, associated rdataset.
289 *
290 *\li 'target' is a valid, dissociated rdataset.
291 *
292 * Ensures:
293 *\li 'target' references the same rdataset as 'source'.
294 */
295
296unsigned int
297dns_rdataset_count(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
298/*%<
299 * Return the number of records in 'rdataset'.
300 *
301 * Requires:
302 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, associated rdataset.
303 *
304 * Returns:
305 *\li The number of records in 'rdataset'.
306 */
307
308isc_result_t
309dns_rdataset_first(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
310/*%<
311 * Move the rdata cursor to the first rdata in the rdataset (if any).
312 *
313 * Requires:
314 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, associated rdataset.
315 *
316 * Returns:
317 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
318 *\li #ISC_R_NOMORE There are no rdata in the set.
319 */
320
321isc_result_t
322dns_rdataset_next(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
323/*%<
324 * Move the rdata cursor to the next rdata in the rdataset (if any).
325 *
326 * Requires:
327 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, associated rdataset.
328 *
329 * Returns:
330 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
331 *\li #ISC_R_NOMORE There are no more rdata in the set.
332 */
333
334void
335dns_rdataset_current(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdata_t *rdata);
336/*%<
337 * Make 'rdata' refer to the current rdata.
338 *
339 * Notes:
340 *
341 *\li The data returned in 'rdata' is valid for the life of the
342 * rdataset; in particular, subsequent changes in the cursor position
343 * do not invalidate 'rdata'.
344 *
345 * Requires:
346 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, associated rdataset.
347 *
348 *\li The rdata cursor of 'rdataset' is at a valid location (i.e. the
349 * result of last call to a cursor movement command was ISC_R_SUCCESS).
350 *
351 * Ensures:
352 *\li 'rdata' refers to the rdata at the rdata cursor location of
353 *\li 'rdataset'.
354 */
355
356isc_result_t
357dns_rdataset_totext(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
358 const dns_name_t *owner_name,
359 bool omit_final_dot,
360 bool question,
361 isc_buffer_t *target);
362/*%<
363 * Convert 'rdataset' to text format, storing the result in 'target'.
364 *
365 * Notes:
366 *\li The rdata cursor position will be changed.
367 *
368 *\li The 'question' flag should normally be #false. If it is
369 * #true, the TTL and rdata fields are not printed. This is
370 * for use when printing an rdata representing a question section.
371 *
372 *\li This interface is deprecated; use dns_master_rdatasettottext()
373 * and/or dns_master_questiontotext() instead.
374 *
375 * Requires:
376 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid rdataset.
377 *
378 *\li 'rdataset' is not empty.
379 */
380
381isc_result_t
382dns_rdataset_towire(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
383 const dns_name_t *owner_name,
384 dns_compress_t *cctx,
385 isc_buffer_t *target,
386 unsigned int options,
387 unsigned int *countp);
388/*%<
389 * Convert 'rdataset' to wire format, compressing names as specified
390 * in 'cctx', and storing the result in 'target'.
391 *
392 * Notes:
393 *\li The rdata cursor position will be changed.
394 *
395 *\li The number of RRs added to target will be added to *countp.
396 *
397 * Requires:
398 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid rdataset.
399 *
400 *\li 'rdataset' is not empty.
401 *
402 *\li 'countp' is a valid pointer.
403 *
404 * Ensures:
405 *\li On a return of ISC_R_SUCCESS, 'target' contains a wire format
406 * for the data contained in 'rdataset'. Any error return leaves
407 * the buffer unchanged.
408 *
409 *\li *countp has been incremented by the number of RRs added to
410 * target.
411 *
412 * Returns:
413 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS - all ok
414 *\li #ISC_R_NOSPACE - 'target' doesn't have enough room
415 *
416 *\li Any error returned by dns_rdata_towire(), dns_rdataset_next(),
417 * dns_name_towire().
418 */
419
420isc_result_t
421dns_rdataset_towiresorted(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
422 const dns_name_t *owner_name,
423 dns_compress_t *cctx,
424 isc_buffer_t *target,
425 dns_rdatasetorderfunc_t order,
426 const void *order_arg,
427 unsigned int options,
428 unsigned int *countp);
429/*%<
430 * Like dns_rdataset_towire(), but sorting the rdatasets according to
431 * the integer value returned by 'order' when called with the rdataset
432 * and 'order_arg' as arguments.
433 *
434 * Requires:
435 *\li All the requirements of dns_rdataset_towire(), and
436 * that order_arg is NULL if and only if order is NULL.
437 */
438
439isc_result_t
440dns_rdataset_towirepartial(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
441 const dns_name_t *owner_name,
442 dns_compress_t *cctx,
443 isc_buffer_t *target,
444 dns_rdatasetorderfunc_t order,
445 const void *order_arg,
446 unsigned int options,
447 unsigned int *countp,
448 void **state);
449/*%<
450 * Like dns_rdataset_towiresorted() except that a partial rdataset
451 * may be written.
452 *
453 * Requires:
454 *\li All the requirements of dns_rdataset_towiresorted().
455 * If 'state' is non NULL then the current position in the
456 * rdataset will be remembered if the rdataset in not
457 * completely written and should be passed on on subsequent
458 * calls (NOT CURRENTLY IMPLEMENTED).
459 *
460 * Returns:
461 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS if all of the records were written.
462 *\li #ISC_R_NOSPACE if unable to fit in all of the records. *countp
463 * will be updated to reflect the number of records
464 * written.
465 */
466
467isc_result_t
468dns_rdataset_additionaldata(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset,
469 dns_additionaldatafunc_t add, void *arg);
470/*%<
471 * For each rdata in rdataset, call 'add' for each name and type in the
472 * rdata which is subject to additional section processing.
473 *
474 * Requires:
475 *
476 *\li 'rdataset' is a valid, non-question rdataset.
477 *
478 *\li 'add' is a valid dns_additionaldatafunc_t
479 *
480 * Ensures:
481 *
482 *\li If successful, dns_rdata_additionaldata() will have been called for
483 * each rdata in 'rdataset'.
484 *
485 *\li If a call to dns_rdata_additionaldata() is not successful, the
486 * result returned will be the result of dns_rdataset_additionaldata().
487 *
488 * Returns:
489 *
490 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
491 *
492 *\li Any error that dns_rdata_additionaldata() can return.
493 */
494
495isc_result_t
496dns_rdataset_getnoqname(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_name_t *name,
497 dns_rdataset_t *neg, dns_rdataset_t *negsig);
498/*%<
499 * Return the noqname proof for this record.
500 *
501 * Requires:
502 *\li 'rdataset' to be valid and #DNS_RDATASETATTR_NOQNAME to be set.
503 *\li 'name' to be valid.
504 *\li 'neg' and 'negsig' to be valid and not associated.
505 */
506
507isc_result_t
508dns_rdataset_addnoqname(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_name_t *name);
509/*%<
510 * Associate a noqname proof with this record.
511 * Sets #DNS_RDATASETATTR_NOQNAME if successful.
512 * Adjusts the 'rdataset->ttl' to minimum of the 'rdataset->ttl' and
513 * the 'nsec'/'nsec3' and 'rrsig(nsec)'/'rrsig(nsec3)' ttl.
514 *
515 * Requires:
516 *\li 'rdataset' to be valid and #DNS_RDATASETATTR_NOQNAME to be set.
517 *\li 'name' to be valid and have NSEC or NSEC3 and associated RRSIG
518 * rdatasets.
519 */
520
521isc_result_t
522dns_rdataset_getclosest(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_name_t *name,
523 dns_rdataset_t *nsec, dns_rdataset_t *nsecsig);
524/*%<
525 * Return the closest encloser for this record.
526 *
527 * Requires:
528 *\li 'rdataset' to be valid and #DNS_RDATASETATTR_CLOSEST to be set.
529 *\li 'name' to be valid.
530 *\li 'nsec' and 'nsecsig' to be valid and not associated.
531 */
532
533isc_result_t
534dns_rdataset_addclosest(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, const dns_name_t *name);
535/*%<
536 * Associate a closest encloset proof with this record.
537 * Sets #DNS_RDATASETATTR_CLOSEST if successful.
538 * Adjusts the 'rdataset->ttl' to minimum of the 'rdataset->ttl' and
539 * the 'nsec' and 'rrsig(nsec)' ttl.
540 *
541 * Requires:
542 *\li 'rdataset' to be valid and #DNS_RDATASETATTR_CLOSEST to be set.
543 *\li 'name' to be valid and have NSEC3 and RRSIG(NSEC3) rdatasets.
544 */
545
546void
547dns_rdataset_settrust(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_trust_t trust);
548/*%<
549 * Set the trust of the 'rdataset' to trust in any in the backing database.
550 * The local trust level of 'rdataset' is also set.
551 */
552
553void
554dns_rdataset_expire(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
555/*%<
556 * Mark the rdataset to be expired in the backing database.
557 */
558
559void
560dns_rdataset_clearprefetch(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset);
561/*%<
562 * Clear the PREFETCH attribute for the given rdataset in the
563 * underlying database.
564 *
565 * In the cache database, this signals that the rdataset is not
566 * eligible to be prefetched when the TTL is close to expiring.
567 * It has no function in other databases.
568 */
569
570void
571dns_rdataset_setownercase(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, const dns_name_t *name);
572/*%<
573 * Store the casing of 'name', the owner name of 'rdataset', into
574 * a bitfield so that the name can be capitalized the same when when
575 * the rdataset is used later. This sets the CASESET attribute.
576 */
577
578void
579dns_rdataset_getownercase(const dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_name_t *name);
580/*%<
581 * If the CASESET attribute is set, retrieve the case bitfield that was
582 * previously stored by dns_rdataset_getownername(), and capitalize 'name'
583 * according to it. If CASESET is not set, do nothing.
584 */
585
586isc_result_t
587dns_rdataset_addglue(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_dbversion_t *version,
588 dns_message_t *msg);
589/*%<
590 * Add glue records for rdataset to the additional section of message in
591 * 'msg'. 'rdataset' must be of type NS.
592 *
593 * In case a successful result is not returned, the caller should try to
594 * add glue directly to the message by iterating for additional data.
595 *
596 * Requires:
597 * \li 'rdataset' is a valid NS rdataset.
598 * \li 'version' is the DB version.
599 * \li 'msg' is the DNS message to which the glue should be added.
600 *
601 * Returns:
602 *\li #ISC_R_SUCCESS
603 *\li #ISC_R_NOTIMPLEMENTED
604 *\li #ISC_R_FAILURE
605 *\li Any error that dns_rdata_additionaldata() can return.
606 */
607
608void
609dns_rdataset_trimttl(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, dns_rdataset_t *sigrdataset,
610 dns_rdata_rrsig_t *rrsig, isc_stdtime_t now,
611 bool acceptexpired);
612/*%<
613 * Trim the ttl of 'rdataset' and 'sigrdataset' so that they will expire
614 * at or before 'rrsig->expiretime'. If 'acceptexpired' is true and the
615 * signature has expired or will expire in the next 120 seconds, limit
616 * the ttl to be no more than 120 seconds.
617 *
618 * The ttl is further limited by the original ttl as stored in 'rrsig'
619 * and the original ttl values of 'rdataset' and 'sigrdataset'.
620 *
621 * Requires:
622 * \li 'rdataset' is a valid rdataset.
623 * \li 'sigrdataset' is a valid rdataset.
624 * \li 'rrsig' is non NULL.
625 */
626
627const char *
628dns_trust_totext(dns_trust_t trust);
629/*%<
630 * Display trust in textual form.
631 */
